WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified display profile for the Samsung Dynamic AMOLED 2X mobile
display technology. It defines the 100% DCI-P3 mobile color volume, peak
brightness up to 1609 nits, LTPO 1-120Hz adaptive refresh, subpixel
layout (Diamond PenTile RGBG), contrast ratio, color accuracy (JNCD),
and HDR certification (HDR10+ Adaptive). This file is the authoritative
reference for GIOP ODTs targeting flagship Samsung smartphones and
tablets.

WHY IT EXISTS
Mobile HDR displays are now primary consumption devices for streaming
content. A GIOP-compliant ODT must know the exact primaries, peak
luminance, and EOTF of these displays to deliver creator-intent images.
This file provides the certified specifications, replacing guesswork
with auditable device parameters.

HOW IT WORKS
This file specifies:
  1. Panel technology (AMOLED, subpixel layout).
  2. Peak luminance and HDR capabilities.
  3. Color gamut and accuracy (JNCD < 0.4).
  4. Refresh rate behaviour and its impact on flicker/ghosting.
  5. EOTF and HDR format support.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Samsung Galaxy S and Tab series (2026 models).
- OTT streaming apps providing device-specific ODTs.
- Mobile HDR mastering QA.

WHO USES IT
- L2 GIOP Engineers: creating mobile ODTs.
- L3 Colorists: previewing mobile deliverables.
