WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Defines the exact color volume and peak luminance of Samsung's flagship
AMOLED panel, enabling automated creation of mobile-specific trim passes.
Removes the discrepancy between studio mastering monitors and mobile OLEDs.

1. PANEL TECHNOLOGY
  Type             : Dynamic AMOLED 2X (emissive OLED)
  Subpixel Layout  : Diamond PenTile RGBG
  Resolution       : up to 1440 x 3200 (WQHD+)
  Typical Size     : 6.8 inch (diagonal)
  Pixel Density    : ~500 PPI

  Diamond PenTile:
    Each pixel has 2 subpixels (Green + alternating Red/Blue).
    Subpixel rendering is handled by the display driver; effective
    resolution for green is full, for red/blue is half. GIOP ODT must
    account for this when rendering fine text/patterns to avoid color
    fringing; a box filter or custom anti-aliasing kernel should be
    applied.

2. PEAK LUMINANCE AND HDR
  Peak Brightness   : 1609 cd/m² (HDR highlight, small area)
  Sustained Brightness : 1200 cd/m² (full-screen white)
  Black Level       : 0 cd/m² (true black, per-pixel emissive off)
  Contrast Ratio    : 2,000,000:1 (certified by VDE)
  HDR Certification : HDR10+ Adaptive with dynamic tone mapping.
                      Vision Booster: enhances visibility under high
                      ambient light (up to 100,000 lux).

  HDR10+ Adaptive:
    Uses real-time ambient light sensor data and content metadata to
    dynamically adjust the tone curve. GIOP provides the MaxCLL/MaxFALL
    metadata and the mastering display peak (e.g., 1000/4000 nit) via
    Dolby Vision XML or HDR10+ JSON. The display's internal processor
    applies the adaptive mapping.

3. COLOR VOLUME AND ACCURACY
  Color Gamut       : 100% DCI-P3 (mobile color volume)
  Color Accuracy    : JNCD < 0.4 (Just Noticeable Color Difference)
  White Point       : D65 (factory calibrated)
  Bit Depth         : 10-bit (internal processing, 8-bit panel + FRC
                      to simulate 10-bit smoothness)

  DCI-P3 primaries (CIE 1931 xy):
    Red   : (0.680, 0.320)
    Green : (0.265, 0.690)
    Blue  : (0.150, 0.060)
    White : D65 (0.3127, 0.3290)

  For GIOP ODT: target DCI-P3 primaries with D65 white point. If the
  content is Rec.2020 or ACES AP1, gamut compression to DCI-P3 is
  required.

4. REFRESH RATE AND LTPO
  Technology        : LTPO (Low-Temperature Polycrystalline Oxide)
  Refresh Rate      : 1 Hz – 120 Hz (adaptive)
    The display dynamically switches refresh rate based on content:
      - 1 Hz : static image (always-on display)
      - 24/30/60/120 Hz : video and gaming
    This has no impact on color but affects perceived motion smoothness.
    GIOP metadata can signal the intended frame rate (24, 30, 60) to
    help the display select an appropriate refresh mode.

5. GIOP ODT RECOMMENDATION
  Target Primaries  : DCI-P3, D65 white
  Target EOTF       : PQ (ST.2084) for HDR, sRGB for SDR
  Peak Luminance    : 1600 nit (PQ), 100 nit (SDR)
  Special Considerations:
    - Apply subpixel-aware anti-aliasing for UI/text overlays.
    - Embed HDR10+ dynamic metadata for adaptive tone mapping.
    - If the content is graded on a 4000 nit BVM-HX3110, a trim pass
      mapping 4000 → 1600 nit must be applied (Level 2 trim).

